    <p>
        Hi Guys<br />
        <b>Please carefully follow these instructions:</b> <br />

        <b>Select Your Hospital:</b> Begin by choosing the hospital from the designated list.<br />
        <b>Select the Stock Location:</b> Click on the provided "Stock Location" link.<br /><br />

        <b>If you are uncertain about the correct stock location:</b><br />

        <b>Consult with the Stock Controller:</b> Reach out to the stock controller for guidance.<br />
        <b>Inquire with the Unit Manager:</b> Alternatively, seek assistance from your unit manager.<br />
        <b>Utilize Clinic Manage:</b> Both the stock controller and unit manager can also verify the correct stock location within the Clinic Manage system.<br />
        <b>Accurate stock location selection is crucial for the proper functioning of the eBilling program.</b><br />
        <br />
        <span style="color:orangered"> Please ensure that you select the correct location to avoid any issues or delays in the billing process.</span><br />



    </p>

    <p>
        <b>Bookmarking and Creating Desktop Shortcuts for the Stock Location Page</b>

        <br />

        This guide will help you easily bookmark the stock location page and create desktop shortcuts for quick access.

        <br /><br />

        <b>1. Bookmarking the Stock Location Page</b>

        <br>

        <b>Navigate to the Page:</b> Open your preferred web browser and navigate to the stock location page.<br />
        <b>Click the Bookmark Icon:</b> Locate the star-shaped bookmark icon in your browser's address bar (usually to the left or right of the URL).<br />
        <b>Name and Save:</b><br />
        Enter a descriptive name for the bookmark (e.g., "Stock Location").<br />
        Choose a folder to save the bookmark in (e.g., "Bookmarks Bar" for easy access).<br />
        Click "Save" or "Done" to confirm.
        <br />
        <br />
        <b>Browser-Specific Instructions:</b><br />

        <b>Chrome:</b> Click the star icon, name the bookmark, choose a folder, and click "Done."<br />
        <b> Firefox:</b> Click the star icon, name the bookmark, choose a folder, and click "Save."<br />
        <b> Safari:</b> Go to "File" > "Add to Bookmarks", name the bookmark, choose a folder, and click "Add."<br />
        <b> Microsoft Edge:</b> Click the star icon, name the bookmark, choose a folder, and click "Save."<br />
        <br /><br />

        <b> 2. Creating a Desktop Shortcut</b>

        <br />

        <b>Copy the URL:</b> Right-click on the URL in the address bar and select "Copy."<br />
        <b>Create a Shortcut:</b><br />
        Right-click on your desktop and select "New" > "Shortcut."<br />
        Paste the copied URL into the "Type the location of the item" field.<br />
        Click "Next."<br />
        Enter a name for the shortcut (e.g., "Stock Location Shortcut").<br />
        Click "Finish."
        <br /><br />

        <b> Browser-Specific Tips:</b><br />

        <b>Chrome, Edge, Firefox:</b><br />
        Some browsers allow you to drag and drop the lock icon (next to the URL) directly onto your desktop to create a shortcut.<br />
        <b>Safari:</b><br />
        Safari might require additional steps or extensions to create desktop shortcuts directly from the browser.


        <br /><br />
        Thanks <br />
        Dev

    </p>
